# Process Flow & Operations

## Standard CRUD Flow

Every resource follows this URL + view pattern:

| Operation | URL Pattern | View Name | HTTP Method |
|-----------|-------------|-----------|-------------|
| List | `/<resource>/` | `<resource>_list` | GET |
| Create | `/<resource>/new/` | `create_<resource>` | GET/POST |
| Detail | `/<resource>/<pk>/` | `<resource>_detail` | GET |
| Edit | `/<resource>/<pk>/edit/` | `edit_<resource>` | GET/POST |
| Delete | `/<resource>/<pk>/delete/` | `delete_<resource>` | POST |
| Export | `/<resource>/<pk>/export/<format>/` | `export_<resource>` | GET |

### URL Naming Convention

```python
app_name = 'myapp'
urlpatterns = [
    path('', views.resource_list, name='resource_list'),
    path('new/', views.create_resource, name='create_resource'),
    path('<int:pk>/', views.resource_detail, name='resource_detail'),
    path('<int:pk>/edit/', views.edit_resource, name='edit_resource'),
    path('<int:pk>/delete/', views.delete_resource, name='delete_resource'),
]
```

## Success Feedback Flow

After successful operations, provide clear feedback:

```python
from django.contrib import messages

def create_resource(request):
    if request.method == 'POST':
        form = ResourceForm(request.POST)
        if form.is_valid():
            obj = form.save(commit=False)
            obj.created_by = request.user
            obj.save()
            messages.success(request, f'{obj} created successfully.')

            if is_htmx_request(request):
                response = HttpResponse(status=200)
                response['HX-Redirect'] = reverse('app:resource_detail', args=[obj.pk])
                return response
            return redirect('app:resource_detail', pk=obj.pk)
```

## Error Handling Flow

### Validation Errors (forms)

Always return `status=400` so HTMX can handle the error state:

```python
if not form.is_valid():
    if is_htmx_request(request):
        return render(request, 'app/partials/_form.html', {'form': form}, status=400)
    return render(request, 'app/create.html', {'form': form})
```

### Permission Errors

Use decorators first, then explicit checks:

```python
@login_required
@role_required('admin', 'doctor')
def sensitive_view(request):
    obj = get_object_or_404(MyModel, pk=pk)
    if request.user.role == 'doctor' and obj.doctor != request.user:
        raise PermissionDenied
```

### Not Found

Use `get_object_or_404()` — never catch `DoesNotExist` and return a custom 404.

## Delete Confirmation Flow

Always confirm before delete. Use HTMX + Alpine modal:

```html
<div x-data="{ confirmDelete: false }">
  <button @click="confirmDelete = true" class="text-red-600 hover:text-red-800">
    <i class="fas fa-trash"></i> Delete
  </button>
  <div x-show="confirmDelete" x-cloak class="fixed inset-0 z-50 flex items-center justify-center bg-black/50">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 max-w-sm mx-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Confirm Delete</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">This action cannot be undone.</p>
      <div class="mt-4 flex justify-end gap-3">
        <button @click="confirmDelete = false"
          class="px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-50">Cancel</button>
        <button hx-post="{% url 'app:delete_resource' obj.pk %}"
          hx-headers='{"X-CSRFToken": "{{ csrf_token }}"}'
          @click="confirmDelete = false"
          class="px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white bg-red-600 rounded-lg hover:bg-red-700">Delete</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Notification Pattern

Create notifications after important operations:

```python
from core.models import Notification

Notification.objects.create(
    user=target_user,
    title='Appointment Confirmed',
    message=f'Your appointment on {appointment.date} has been confirmed.',
    notification_type='appointment',
)
```

## Status Transitions

When resources have statuses, enforce valid transitions:

```
pending → approved / rejected
approved → completed / cancelled
draft → submitted → reviewed → approved / rejected
```

Always validate transitions server-side. Never trust client-sent status values.

## Search & Filter Pattern

Consistent across all list views:

```python
def resource_list(request):
    qs = MyModel.objects.all()

    # Role filtering
    if request.user.role == 'student':
        qs = qs.filter(user=request.user)

    # Search
    search = request.GET.get('search', '').strip()
    if search:
        qs = qs.filter(
            Q(field1__icontains=search) | Q(field2__icontains=search)
        )

    # Status filter
    status = request.GET.get('status', '')
    if status:
        qs = qs.filter(status=status)

    # Status totals for badges
    status_totals = {
        'all': qs.count(),
        'pending': qs.filter(status='pending').count(),
        'completed': qs.filter(status='completed').count(),
    }

    # Pagination
    paginator = Paginator(qs, 15)
    page_obj = paginator.get_page(request.GET.get('page', 1))

    ctx = {
        'page_obj': page_obj,
        'status_totals': status_totals,
        'search': search,
        'current_status': status,
    }

    if is_htmx_request(request):
        return render(request, 'app/partials/_list.html', ctx)
    return render(request, 'app/list.html', ctx)
```

## Form Submission Redirects

| Context | Redirect Method |
|---------|----------------|
| Standard POST | `return redirect('app:detail', pk=obj.pk)` |
| HTMX POST | `response['HX-Redirect'] = reverse('app:detail', args=[obj.pk])` |
| HTMX inline update | Return partial HTML fragment with `status=200` |
| HTMX delete | Return empty with `status=200` + `HX-Trigger` for list refresh |
